text.section:
A credit grantor may require a consumer borrower to pay for services rendered by the credit grantor's attorney only if the attorney's fee:
Is limited to legal services attributable to processing and closing the loan and not to unrelated services performed by the attorney for the credit grantor;
If in excess of $100, is supported by a statement provided to the borrower at or prior to settlement that:
Describes the services performed;
Sets forth the time spent by the attorney and the hourly rate or other basis for determining the fee;
States that the legal services are being performed on behalf of the credit grantor and not on behalf of the consumer borrower; and
States that the services are being paid for by the consumer borrower;
Is reasonable on the basis of the legal services performed; and
Is separately itemized on the loan settlement sheet and identified as a fee to the credit grantor's attorney.

section.section:
Subject to the requirements of subsection (b) of this section, this subsection may not be construed to prohibit a credit grantor from requiring a consumer borrower to pay for:
Preparation of loan closing documents;
Title insurance;
Review of documents prepared by the borrower's attorney; or
Attendance at settlement by the credit grantor's attorney.
